org.unc.lac.baboon.actioncontroller

Class ActionController

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.unc.lac.baboon.actioncontroller.ActionController
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    HappeningActionController, TaskActionController

    public abstract class ActionController
extends java.lang.Object
    An ActionController is an abstract class defined by
    • An object instance.
    • A TaskController or HappeningController annotated method, member of the class of the object instance.
    • A set of GuardProvider annotated methods, member of the class of the object instance, that are organized in a Map indexed by the guard name corresponding to the GuardProvider.value().
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Ariel Ivan Rabinovich, Juan Jose Arce Giacobbe

      • guardProviderMethodsMap

        protected java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.reflect.Method> guardProviderMethodsMap
        The Map of GuardProvider annotated methods of this actionController. They must be members of {#actionObject} class. The map is indexed by guard names, taken from GuardProvider.value().

    • Constructor Detail

      • ActionController

        public ActionController(java.lang.Object actionObject,
                        java.lang.reflect.Method actionMethod)
                 throws MultipleGuardProvidersException,
                        InvalidGuardProviderMethod,
                        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Constructor. Sets the actionObject, the actionMethod and finally resolves the GuardProvider annotated methods of the actionObject and saves them into guardProviderMethodsMap
        Parameters:
        actionObject - The object instance of the actionController
        actionMethod - A TaskController or HappeningController annotated method for this actionController, must be a member of {#actionObject} class
        Throws:
        MultipleGuardProvidersException -
        • When more than one GuardProvider annotated methods are referred to the same guard name
        InvalidGuardProviderMethod -
        • When a GuardProvider annotated method has a return type other than boolean
        • When a GuardProvider annotated method requires arguments
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException -
        • When the actionObject provided is null
        • When the actionMethod provided is null

        public boolean getGuardValue(java.lang.String guardName)
                      throws java.lang.IllegalAccessException,
                             java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException
        This method returns the value of the guard by executing the GuardProvider annotated method associated with the guard. It is intended to be used by the framework only, the user should not call this method.
        Parameters:
        guardName - The name of the guard whose value is to be known
        Returns:
        The value of the guard
        Throws:
        java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException - Error when invoking a GuardProvider method.
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - Error when accessing a GuardProvider method.

      • hasGuardProvider

        public boolean hasGuardProvider(java.lang.String guardName)
        This method returns a boolean value indicating the presence of a GuardProvider annotated method to handle the guardName provided as argument
        Parameters:
        guardName - the guard name associated to the GuardProvider annotated method, whose presence is to be tested.
        Returns:
        true if there is a GuardProvider annotated method associated to the guardName
